Hantavirus infections in Scandinavia
------------------------------------
The recent report of Hemorrhagic Fever and Renal Syndrome (HFRS)
activity in Finland [see ProMED-mail Archive Reference below] reminds
us that this country continues to report the highest rates for
hantavirus infection in the region. In the attached graph, I've
compared disease statistics for Scandinavia and adjacent countries: see,
<http://exhibit.gideononline.com/hanta-finland.jpg>

The source of the information is the Gideon database at:
<http://www.gideononline.com/blog/2008/12/18/hantavirus-infections-in-scandinavia/>.

--
Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center, Israel
